ups were all positive (0.05\u20130.4) with more narrow uncertainties. Beta diversity may, therefore, be a more reliable and information-rich indicator than alpha diversity in understanding animal community response to landscape change. Patterns in beta diversity were primarily driven by turnover instead of species loss or gain, indicating that wood extraction generates habitats that support different biological communities.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Jones, Gavin M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Brosi, Berry", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Evans, Jason M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gottlieb, Isabel G. W.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Loy, Xingwen", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "N\u00fa\u00f1ez\u2010Regueiro, Mauricio M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ober, Holly K.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pienaar, Elizabeth", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pillay, Rajeev", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pisarello, Kathryn", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Smith, Lora L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fletcher, Robert J.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/82793d62e60dc8ea7ce152e63d005f26", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/de3461d82a5492457da2159e2b20c0d7762d6de1ab0498eedba13c98abc2e559", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/6US4FLCH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/6US4FLCH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6d21ef98695c733cdd8cdf80eb18d8f8!/b257954-260421", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relati